SET 1 is acoustic Dead; this is the complete set.
Pigpen plays piano on Truckin, Ripple & New Speedway. Jerry switches to
electric guitar on New Speedway. David Nelson plays mandolin on Rosalie
McFall, Cold Jordan & Swing Low. Marmaduke adds bass vocals to Cold Jordan
and Swing Low. The introduction goes: "Good evening and welcome to the
Fillmore West. Tonight you're going to spend an evening with the Grateful
Dead."

reviews.review_text: Thank you! Thank you for this very wonderful new version of an important show from an important period in the bands evolution.  To me, every one of the acoustic/electric shows is a gift from the gods. Here we also have first Ripple and Broke Down Palace recordings. They have may have broke the songs at earlier unrecorded shows.  I marvel at the bands abilty to cover all this divergent material so thoroughly. Especially Jerry - three bands, three instruments. Etc. I also love hearing the audience - it provides atmospherics that are really priceless. I listen to the acoustic with pure direct settings and the electric 7 channel enhanced. Five stars for the set list, the atmospherics and the quality of this version.
